

Lab 3, Essential file management tools:

1. Create a directory structute /tmp/files/pictures, /tmp/files/photos and /tmp/files/viveos

2. Copy all files that have a name starting with an a or b or c from /etc to /tmp/files

3. From /tmp/files, move all files that have a name starting with an a or b to /tmp/files/photos, and files with a name starting with a c to /tmp/files/videos

4. Find all files in /etc that have a size smaller than 1000 bytes and copy those to /tmp/pictures

5. In tmp/files, create a symbolic link to /var

6. Create a compressed archive file of the /home directory

7. Extract this compressed archive with relative file names in /tpm/archive









